---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const lastUpdated = '18 May 2026'
---

<Layout
  title="Terms"
  description="Terms of use for Union — the prayer app from Side8."
>
  <article class="prose-union">
    <h1 class="font-prayer text-5xl text-union-charcoal">Terms</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-union-secondary">
      Last updated: {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Union is provided by Side8 Limited (&ldquo;Side8&rdquo;,
      &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;). By using Union you agree to
      these terms. They&apos;re intentionally short. If you don&apos;t
      agree, please don&apos;t use the app.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      What Union is
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      A prayer companion. You describe what&apos;s on your heart; we
      suggest prayers from the Christian tradition that fit. We may
      add a short pastoral note alongside the prayers. We are not
      providing pastoral counselling, medical advice, mental health
      treatment, or any other form of professional service. If you
      are in distress, please contact a qualified professional or a
      crisis line.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Acceptable use
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Use Union for personal prayer and reflection. Don&apos;t try to
      reverse-engineer it, abuse the AI components, attempt to extract
      our prayer corpus in bulk, or use the app to harass, defraud, or
      harm anyone.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Account, content, and deletion
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      You&apos;re responsible for keeping your sign-in email secure.
      You retain ownership of everything you write into Union — your
      check-ins, reflections, and answered notes. We process that
      content only to provide the app, as described in our
      <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="/privacy">privacy
      page</a>. You can delete your account and all related data at any
      time from Settings → Delete account.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Prayer corpus
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      The prayers Union suggests are drawn from historical and
      contemporary Christian sources. Public-domain texts (the Book of
      Common Prayer, classical collects, ancient prayers) are quoted
      as-is. Where modern prayers are included, we believe we have the
      necessary permissions or rely on fair use; if you believe a
      prayer is included in error, email us and we&apos;ll review.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Availability and changes
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Union is offered as-is. We may change features, take it down for
      maintenance, or retire it. We&apos;ll give reasonable notice
      before any retirement so you can export your saved prayers.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Liability
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      To the extent permitted by law, Side8 is not liable for indirect
      or consequential losses arising from your use of the app. Nothing
      in these terms limits liability for things the law doesn&apos;t
      let us limit (such as death or personal injury caused by our
      negligence, or fraud).
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Governing law
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales.
      Disputes go to the courts of England and Wales.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Changes to these terms
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      If we make a material change we&apos;ll update the
      &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date above and surface a notice in
      the app for at least a week.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Contact
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="mailto:hello@side8.io"
      >hello@side8.io</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
